1. mkdir - New directory
2. ls - List the content in the directory
3. cd - change directory
4. touch - create an empty file
5. cat > - display the content
         - create content
         - merge two files and copy to another file
6. ll - Long list
7. pwd - present working directory
8. cp - copy files
9. mv - move files
10 . cp-r - copy directories
11. mv-r - move directories
12. head - display top 10 lines of file
13. vi - create new file with content
14. tail - to display bottom 10 lines in a file
15. clear - clear screen
16 . History - display history
17. hostname - display hostname
18. hostname -i - display host IP
19. rm - removes file in directories
20. rm-r / rmdir - removes directories
21. unname-r - Kernal version
22. cat /etc/os-release - Os information
23. hostnamectl set-hostname - to set hostnmae to linux server
24. su root - to see hostname
25. exec bash - to see hostname
26. yum install - to install packages
27. tree - to see structure of directory
28. cd .. - get back to previous directory
29. ctrl+l - clears screen but keeps data
30. ping - checks the network connectivity of the server
31. ip-a - ip address of the server

